    "body": "@thestinger We would have to split slices into their components at the top of functions, and then use scoped aliasing metadata with a scope corresponding to the whole function. This is morally equivalent to changing the calling convention to pass slices as separate components. It isn't sound to use scoped metadata with a scope of the entire function for every `&mut` that appears in the function, since there may be nonoverlapping borrows of the same path.\n",
